Title: Login link redirects repeatedly to the same page instead of opening authentication screen

## Preconditions

- User is not logged in

- Website is accessed via desktop browser

- Login option is visible on the homepage

## Environment

- Browser: Firefox

- OS: Ubuntu

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Access the website homepage

2. Click on "Fazer Login"

3. After redirection, click on "Fazer Login" again

## Expected Result

User should be redirected to a login page with authentication fields

## Actual Result

User is redirected to a page with URL containing "?page_id=6"

Clicking "Fazer Login" again repeats the same behavior, preventing access to a login screen

## Severity

High

## Severity Justification: Core authentication flow is broken, preventing user from acessing the system entirely

## Priority

High

## Type

Bug

## ISO 25010 Category

Functional Suitability

## ISO 25010 Subcategory

Functional Correctness

## Secondary Impact

Usability – Operability
